{"lemma":"مُنْكَبُّو","slug":"مُنْكَبُّو","root":"ك.ب.ب","root_slug":"ك-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ب-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40458"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%91%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, flank"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shoulder joint"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"highland, upland"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/man.kib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40458","headword_ar":"مَنْكِبٌ","root":"nkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(masc., Lh, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shoulder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of junction of the os humeri and the scapula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) in a man &c; (ISd:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of junction of the os humeri and the scapula and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendon called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habolu AlEaAtiqi","text_ar":"حَبْلُ العَاتِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a man and a bird and any other thing. (TA.) [It seems to be regarded by some as originally signifying “ a place of deflection: ” but] Sb denies its being a noun of place, because, were it so, it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokabN","text_ar":"مَنْكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": he does not allow it to be included in the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToliEN","text_ar":"مَطْلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is extr. Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAkibu","text_ar":"مَنَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $adiydu AlmanaAkibi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شَدِيدُ المَنَاكِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man having a strong shoulder:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the sing. were applied to denote each part of the joint, and the pl. to denote the whole. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haz~uwA manaAkibahumo","text_ar":"هَزُّوا مَنَاكِبَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They shook their shoulderjoints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they rejoiced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiyAarukumo A^alayonukumo manaAkiba fiY","text_ar":"خِياَرُكُمْ اَلَيْنُكُمْ مَنَاكِبَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The best of you are the most easy of you in the shoulder-joints in prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of you who keep"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most readily"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"give room to such as enter the rank in prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibu Alfarasi","text_ar":"مَنْكِبُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"β","text_ar":"β","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in Pegasus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibu AljawozaA'i","text_ar":"مَنْكِبُ الجَوْزَاءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bright, and very great star, a, in the right shoulderjoint, of Orion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibN","text_ar":"مَنْكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adjacent, part, quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAkibu","text_ar":"مَنَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sironaA fiY mnkbK mina AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"سِرْنَا فِى منكبٍ مِنَ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We proceeded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeyed, along a side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lateral part, of the land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina","text_ar":"مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabali","text_ar":"الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) so in the Kur, lxvii. 15, the pl. signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the earth: (Fr:) or its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) which last signification in this case is preferred by Az: (TA:) or the sing. signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the earth or land. (S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmanaAkibN","text_ar":"المَنَاكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The feathers next after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAdim","text_ar":"قَوَادِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [which latter are the anterior, or primary, feathers of a bird's wing;] (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the feathers of the wing of a vulture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eagle that are next after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwAdm","text_ar":"قوادم"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are the strongest and most excellent of the feathers; (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feathers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the wing of a bird, next after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwAdm","text_ar":"قوادم"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the four secondary feathers of the wing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the wing of a bird are twenty leathers: the first of them are those called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqwAdm","text_ar":"القوادم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmnAkb","text_ar":"المناكب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxawaA fiY","text_ar":"الخَوَا فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abAhiru","text_ar":"الاَباهِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkulaY","text_ar":"الكُلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) It is a word without a sing. (K.) ISd says, I know not a sing. to it; but by analogy it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibN","text_ar":"مَنْكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomahu bimanaAkiba rAa$a","text_ar":"سَهْمَهُ بِمَنَاكِبَ راَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He feathered his arrow with feathers such as are described above."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokibN","text_ar":"مَنْكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyfN","text_ar":"عَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intendant, superintendent, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an aider, helper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people: (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistant of an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eryf","text_ar":"عريف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one below an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eryf","text_ar":"عريف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAth:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurafaA'u","text_ar":"عُرَفَاءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eryf","text_ar":"عريف"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Lth, S:) there being over so many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErfA'","text_ar":"عرفاء"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnkb","text_ar":"منكب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariyfN","text_ar":"عَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAkibu","text_ar":"مَنَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["ISd","K","TA","Fr","Zj","Msb","IAth","Lth","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}